## Acceptance criteria

- `MetadataLimits` rejects every zero/inconsistent configuration and preserves each exact caller-supplied bound; `ExifMetadataInput` has no unbounded/default construction path.
- `MetadataInput` is object-safe and byte-oriented. It receives explicit `InputFormat`; no path or extension enters the API, and mismatched explicit format/signature returns the documented typed error.
- The reviewed JPEG, PNG, and TIFF fixtures each produce equal canonical `ImageMetadata` containing exactly the same nine fields in #28 rank order and exact reviewed values.
- A valid supported image with no EXIF returns `ImageMetadata::empty()`. XMP-only, IPTC-only, GPS-only, ICC-only, MakerNote-only, thumbnail, and unknown-tag data do not populate an extension bag or alter supported values.
- Duplicate JPEG APP1 EXIF payloads, duplicate PNG `eXIf` chunks, and duplicate supported fields return exact typed duplicate errors; the reader never silently chooses first or last.
- Text removes only trailing encoded NUL padding and otherwise round-trips exact UTF-8 bytes. Invalid UTF-8, interior NUL, empty-after-padding, and over-limit text return canonical-field-attributed typed errors.
- Rationals remain exact and reduce through `PositiveRational`; zero components, overflow, nonzero ISO overflow/zero, and orientation outside `1..=8` return field-attributed typed errors without floating-point conversion.
- Source, EXIF payload, segment/chunk, nesting, total-entry, and per-value limits each have a deterministic fixture that returns the exact limit category before unbounded traversal or allocation.
- Truncated containers, invalid offsets/types/counts, cyclic/deep IFDs, and malformed EXIF return typed errors without panic, hang, partial metadata, or leaked parser errors.
- No pixel orientation, ICC/gamma/color transform, timezone/calendar conversion, metadata writing, catalog mutation, output encoding, filesystem access, async work, UI behavior, or inherited darktable metadata code is introduced.
- `cargo tree` and the boundary test show parser dependencies only in `rusttable-metadata`; `rusttable-core` remains free of normal third-party dependencies.
- No local unsafe Rust, FFI, C/C++ build step, networked test, sleep, wall-clock assertion, randomness-dependent behavior, or handwritten Rust file over 1,000 lines is introduced.

## One-PR scope

Deliver exactly one focused PR that adds the bounded parser-neutral metadata input contract and one concrete EXIF adapter for JPEG/PNG/classic-TIFF bytes, records failing-first evidence, passes every listed validation command, closes only this issue, and is squash-merged. Do not add metadata writing, output preservation, orientation application, source-file reading, import registration, processing integration, UI behavior, or support for XMP/IPTC/GPS/ICC/MakerNotes in this PR.

## Why

RustTable’s repository settings already permit squash merges and disable merge commits/rebase merges, and `.githooks/pre-commit-guard` blocks ordinary local commits on `main`/`master`. Those controls do not constitute a reviewable server-side contract: local hooks can be bypassed, direct API/Git pushes never execute them, and the repository currently has no committed, regression-tested definition of the protection expected for `main`.

The stable `rust-pr / validate` check exists after completed #14 / PR #69, and completed #17 / PR #82 now validates every integrated `main` commit. #81 must first make the shared PR/main fast gate fail correctly. Once the check is trustworthy, GitHub should enforce PR-only integration, the required check, linear history, and destructive-update protections rather than relying on contributor discipline.

## How

- Write failing policy-normalization tests first and record the initial red command/output in the implementation PR.
- Add a dependency-free Bun module under `scripts/github/` with explicit `check` and `apply` commands for `cgasgarth/RustTable`.
- Read the expected repository and `main`-branch policy from typed constants in that module; do not add a second configuration format or a third-party dependency.
- The expected repository settings must require:
  - default branch `main`;
  - squash merge enabled;
  - merge commits disabled;
  - rebase merges disabled.
- The expected `main` protection must require:
  - changes through pull requests, while retaining zero mandatory approvals so the single-maintainer repository is not deadlocked;
  - the exact status context `rust-pr / validate` with strict/up-to-date branch checking;
  - enforcement for administrators;
  - conversation resolution before merge;
  - linear history;
  - force pushes disabled;
  - branch deletion disabled;
  - no actor/team/app bypass allowance.
- Do not require code-owner review, signed commits, deployments, merge queue, or a second status context in this PR. Those policies need separate evidence and must not make the sole maintainer unable to merge.
- Implement `check` as a read-only, fail-closed comparison against the GitHub REST responses. It must report every drifted field with expected and observed values, tolerate irrelevant response fields, and redact authentication material from all output.
- Implement `apply` as an explicit owner-operated action that updates only the listed repository merge settings and `main` protection fields, then re-fetches and verifies the resulting state. Require an explicit `--apply cgasgarth/RustTable main` confirmation; a missing or mismatched repository/branch argument must make no request.
- Use `GH_TOKEN` or `GITHUB_TOKEN` only from the invoking process environment. Never persist a token, print it, add it to a workflow, or introduce a repository secret.
- Add deterministic Bun tests with fixture responses and a fake transport covering:
  - exact compliant state;
  - each repository merge-setting drift;
  - missing required PR protection;
  - missing/wrong required status context and non-strict status checking;
  - administrator bypass;
  - unresolved-conversation allowance;
  - non-linear history;
  - force-push/deletion allowance;
  - actor/team/app bypass entries;
  - multiple simultaneous drifts reported together;
  - failed update and failed post-update verification;
  - confirmation mismatch making zero write requests;
  - token redaction.
- Add root package scripts for the deterministic test and the explicit live check/apply commands. Keep `package.json` dependency-free and preserve exact `bun@1.3.14`.
- Run only the deterministic fixture test once in `scripts/precommit-fast.sh` and once in `scripts/pr-ci.sh`; never call the live GitHub API from pre-commit, pre-push, or GitHub Actions.
- Apply the policy to the real repository during this issue’s implementation and attach the final read-only check output to the PR.
- Do not modify product code, workflow job contents, CODEOWNERS, issue/PR templates, dependency policy, inherited workflow files, or release automation in this issue.

## Sequencing and dependencies

- Depends on completed #14 / PR #69 for the stable `rust-pr / validate` context.
- Builds on completed #17 / PR #82 for the current integrated-main workflow state, but does not require that push-only workflow as a pull-request status check.
- **Blocked by #81**, which makes the required PR check fail closed for every cheap validation command.
- Should land immediately after #81 and before #74. #74 separately retires inherited darktable workflow files and freezes the executable workflow inventory.

## Validation

- `bun run test:repository-policy`
- `bun run check:repository-policy -- cgasgarth/RustTable main`
- owner-operated apply command with the explicit repository/branch confirmation
- immediate post-apply read-only check
- `bash scripts/precommit-fast.sh`
- `bash scripts/prepush-fast.sh`
- `bash scripts/pr-ci.sh`
- `bash scripts/main-ci.sh`
- `git diff --check`

Record the clean pre-commit and hosted PR durations after adding the deterministic fixture test. After protection is applied, verify through temporary non-destructive attempts that a direct update to `main` is rejected and that a PR without a passing `rust-pr / validate` result cannot merge.

## Acceptance criteria

- Fixture tests fail closed and report field-specific expected/observed drift for every listed repository and branch-protection rule, including multiple drift fields in one run.
- The apply path makes no write request without the exact `--apply cgasgarth/RustTable main` confirmation, never logs a token, and fails when the post-update state is still noncompliant.
- The real repository reports `main` as default, squash-only merge methods, PR-required integration with zero mandatory approvals, strict `rust-pr / validate`, administrator enforcement, conversation resolution, linear history, and disabled force-push/deletion behavior with no bypass actors.
- A direct push/update attempt to `main` is rejected server-side even when local hooks are bypassed.
- A PR whose `rust-pr / validate` check is missing or failing is not mergeable; a clean passing PR remains mergeable by the sole maintainer without a second reviewer.
- Only deterministic fixture tests run in local/PR validation; no live API call, admin token, repository write permission, or secret is added to any workflow.
- `package.json` remains free of dependencies and retains exact Bun `1.3.14`.
- Clean pre-commit remains at or below 30 seconds, pre-push at or below 60 seconds, and the PR workflow at or below 150 seconds.
- The existing merge-to-`main` workflow continues to run on every integrated SHA after protection is applied.

## Exactly one-PR scope

Deliver all and only the typed repository-policy checker/applicator, deterministic tests, fast-test wiring, and the corresponding real `main` protection update from one dedicated issue worktree in one pull request. That PR must close only this issue and be squash-merged to `main`.

