## Superseded

This issue’s adapter/device capability, limit, behavioral probe, and device-policy scope is now fully consolidated into #290, **Create the rusttable-gpu crate and WGPU instance/device selection**.

The earlier split would have created two competing capability snapshots and required a second PR to re-probe the device immediately after initialization. #290 now owns:

- normalized adapter/device/driver identity;
- deterministic adapter ranking and minimal device requests;
- required/optional feature and limit capture;
- behavioral qualification for advertised capabilities;
- semantic `GpuCapabilitySnapshot` and `GpuFeaturePlan` APIs;
- backend/platform policy, CPU-only behavior, fault generation, and bounded recreation;
- capability receipts, fixtures, and real backend smoke tests.

Do not implement this issue separately. All references and dependencies should use #290.

Closes #492

Implements the issue-scoped capability ownership reconciliation contract:

- adds deterministic, hash-addressed plan and optimistic apply flows;
- matches explicit capability metadata and reviewed compatibility identities before title similarity;
- rejects incomplete or ambiguous creations, derives reviewed milestone policy, and records label/milestone actions;
